Jessica, Victoria McGowan (now Fleming), Vic Pace, and myself engage in an ongoing grammar joke/bit since we met in Junior year (I'm 35 years old as of this date);

Jess and Mag both started with a sort of high-airy/fancy speaking manner of the triptych absurd image and play with moat/boat/goat absurd situations; 

rhyme triplet evolved into saying, "Oh, that is mo!"; this evolved into leaving off the word after the verbs, and the sentences could take the shape of:
--that is gonna be!
--you're going to have a!

understanding and thoughts so far?
